lead_paragraph: The F.B.I. said Thursday that there was no indication that the man who ambushed a Philadelphia policeman was part of an organized terror cell.

headline.print_headline: Pennsylvania: No Terror Cell in Ambush, F.B.I. Says
headline.main: Pennsylvania: No Terror Cell in Ambush, F.B.I. Says

snippet: The F.B.I. said Thursday that there was no indication that the man who ambushed a Philadelphia policeman was part of an organized terror cell.
abstract: Federal Bureau of Investigation reports no indication that Edward Archer of Yeadon, Pa, who attacked Philadelphia Police Officer Jesse Hartnett, was part of organized terror cell; Yeadon, who faces attempted murder charge, says he was acting in name of Islam.
